# Incremental & Review-Friendly Development

- Prefer small, focused diffs: one feature/fix/refactor per edit.
- ALWAYS explain changes first in a <PLAN> block: what, why, impact, tests needed.
- Include inline comments in code for non-obvious parts.
- After edits, suggest running tests/lint/build (e.g., dotnet test, npm run lint).
- If large refactor needed, propose steps in numbered list and ask for confirmation before full implementation.
- Use diff-friendly patterns: avoid renaming files/classes unless explicitly requested.
